And this is what [D7]she said
She said a woman [C]came by with a letter for [D7]you
And this is what the letter [G]said
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
Dear John please Johnny please come [D7]home
I need your love and the kids they gotta be [G]fed
And John if you don't hurry back I'll be [D7]gone
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
Yes that's what the letter said
The letter that Johnny Walker [G]read
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
Then John he got up from the [D7]table
[C]Slowly so slowly he walked [D7]outside
He was [G]thinking of his wife and little children back at [D7]home
And [C]how his drinking had [D7]ruined their [G]lives
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
Then John he stared off into that street [D7]light
